qas.question: What percentage of Kathmandu residents are Chettris?
What is the third largest ethnic group in Kathmandu?
What Kathmandu industry is particularly known for its English speakers?
Along with Nepali, what is Kathmandu's main language?

context: The largest ethnic groups are Newar (29.6%), Matwali (25.1% Sunuwar, Gurung, Magars, Tamang etc.), <a1_0>Khas Brahmins<a1_0/> (20.51%) and Chettris (<a0_0>18.5<a0_0/>%) . Tamangs originating from surrounding hill districts can be seen in Kathmandu. More recently, other hill ethnic groups and Caste groups from Terai have come to represent a substantial proportion of the city's population. The major languages are Nepali and <a4_0>Nepal Bhasa<a4_0/>, while English is understood by many, particularly in the <a3_0>service<a3_0/> industry. The major religions are <a2_0>Hinduism and Buddhism<a2_0/>.
